The social card of a resident of the Ivanovo region is recognized as an electronic means of payment.
The amendments provide for the preservation of the privilege for travel in public passenger transport.
From September 24, the procedure for organizing preferential travel for citizens using the social card of a resident of the Ivanovo region is changing.
According to the press service of the Russian government in the Ivanovo region, the changes provide for the preservation of benefits for travel in public passenger transport and bring the scheme of mutual settlements on the social card in line with the requirements of Federal Law No. 161 of the Federal Law "On the National Payment System".
At the same time, the social card of a resident of the Ivanovo region is recognized as an electronic means of payment.
Accordingly, the conditions for its application change.
So, the replenishment limit is now set not in trips, as before, but in the amount of money, with the preservation of winter and summer periods - in winter no more than 400 rubles, in the summer - no more than 800 rubles for the current month.
Now the owners of the social card on the receipts issued in transport will need to track not the number of remaining trips, but the balance of funds.
The cost of preferential travel for citizens will be 1/2 of the tariff in force at the carrier.
The remaining half of the fare is reimbursed by the regional budget.
The schedule of replenishment of the social card with funds remains the same - in the period from the 24th day of the previous month to the 23rd day of the current month.
The new order of travel on a social card will have a number of advantages.
So, it becomes possible to keep detailed records of spending money on a social card with an accuracy of up to a penny.
In addition, it becomes possible to return credited, but unspent funds.
We also add that the scheme of mutual settlements with carriers becomes transparent, since now half of the fare is paid by a citizen, and exactly the same amount is reimbursed to the carrier by the budget.
No commission will be charged when depositing funds on the card.
In turn, Vasily Silkin, Deputy Head of the Department of Road Management and Transport of the Ivanovo Region, said that in 2014 more than 33 million trips were made in the region using a social card, in 2015 - almost 25 million trips.
In the regional budget, more than 470 million rubles are provided for the provision of preferential travel for citizens using a social card.
As of September 1, the amount of compensation for these purposes amounted to more than 312 million rubles.
