Why are eyelids often irritated and reddened?
Answers ophthalmologist Tatyana Levashova:
Our eyelids are screens that protect the eyeball from the many small particles that settle on them.
Forgetting about the regular cleaning of the eyelids, we often contribute to the development of blepharitis.
The solution is simple:
do not rub your eyes with dirty hands, carry a special wet wipe for the eyelids;
at least 1-2 times a day, clean the edges of the eyelids from harmful substances accumulated in them during the day.
Cleansing procedures are useful to supplement with warm compresses with decoctions of medicinal herbs (sage, chamomile), thinning the thick secretion of the sebaceous glands, and then massage the edges of the eyelids, which should be carried out in a circular motion of the fingertips;
when washing off makeup, do not use alcohol-containing products.
They dry and dehydrate the skin and contribute to an even greater thickening of the secretion of the sebaceous glands.
