Prisons are asked to create separate blocks for transgender people.
In October 2015, the Public Council under the Federal Penitentiary Service (FSIN) for the Protection of the Rights of Convicts will discuss, among other issues, the possibility of creating separate blocks for transgender and transvestites in colonies.
About this "Izvestia" told a member of the council Vladislav Grib.
In his opinion, depending on the total number of convicts in Russia who have not decided on their gender, it is possible to provide separate cells, blocks in domestic prisons or even (if there are many such criminals) in the future to create a special colony for transsexuals.
However, Vladislav Hryb emphasizes that it is possible to determine citizens to serve their sentences in such isolated places only after the convicts pass the appropriate medical examinations that will prove that the offender is really a person who identifies himself as a representative of the opposite sex.
Vladislav Hryb is confident that the isolation of transgender people from other prisoners will ensure the safety of those serving sentences.
According to him, the proposed practice is successfully operating abroad: in pre-trial detention centers (where defendants are held until the court decision) there are separate cells for transgender people, and in correctional institutions - special blocks.
Today, this is the only way out when working with such criminals.
Definitely they need to be isolated, since the presence of transvestites and transgenders in ordinary cells is dangerous for them, this is suffering for their families and a sea of problems for FSIN employees.
Humiliation of trance on the part of fellow inmates is guaranteed, - says Vladislav Grib.
Depending on how large the city is, how many criminals with an uncertain gender, you need to calculate where to distribute them.
Separate pre-trial detention centers are definitely not needed - only cells, blocks in prisons.
Yes, a separate colony is possible if there are a lot of transgender people.
As Grib explained, the block can contain 50 or 100 people, and if one specialized corps is created in Russia, then transgender prisoners will be able to go there from any regions to serve their sentences.
Citizens are held in a pre-trial detention center at the place where the crime was committed, so the receipt of transvestites or transgenders from other subjects during the investigation and trial is unrealistic, but to introduce such a practice for those already convicted in a separate colony - yes, - Grib believes.
Recall that on the eve of law enforcement officers could not decide in which detention center - male or female - to determine the 24-year-old transsexual Dmitry Kozhukov (known as Alina Davis), detained for drug possession, because of which a man with a girlish appearance was not arrested.
He was released home on his own recognizance.
This news was widely discussed in social networks and the media, since there really is no mechanism for keeping transgender people in pre-trial detention centers and colonies in Russia.
Russian human rights activist, activist of the LGBT movement (LGBT - lesbian, gay, bisexual, transsexual) Nikolai Alekseev supported the idea of creating special places for transgender people to serve their sentences, noting that abroad it is also possible to determine people in the colony - male or female - depending on their own desire.
Given the atmosphere in Russian prisons, the proposal is correct.
Yes, this is a very small percentage, but there is a problem, as well as the issue of ensuring security for homosexuals in prisons," Alekseev said.
Prisons should be safe, so separate blocks could be made in the name of this and for homosexuals, especially since there are more of them in prisons than transgender people.
At the same time, Alexeyev doubts that there will be many citizens in Russia who are ready to pose as transsexuals in order to get into a different colony from ordinary ones.
Of course, it is possible to introduce a medical examination before placing people in transgender colonies, but not always everything is unambiguous.
For example, in the United States, one of the prisoners Chelsea Manning looked like a man, and already in prison he said that he wanted to change his gender," Alekseev said.
A person can feel like anyone.
But as long as there are no separate places to serve sentences for transgender people, I doubt that prison staff will seriously think about the safety of such people and delve into the intricacies of their orientation or gender identification.
At the same time, Boris Lordkipanidze, an international expert on reproductive health in the territory of the Russian Federation, noted that the introduction of a new system for the distribution of transsexual criminals in the colony could greatly delay the beginning of serving sentences by convicts.
A commission is created - this is a question of sexology, psychiatrists conduct long-term observations, this is not one test, on the basis of which a highly accurate conclusion is made.
Today's psychiatry capabilities allow for this.
Therefore, even before changing sex, potential patients always undergo such examinations - they accurately show whether gender reassignment with surgical intervention is a necessary measure," says Lordkipanidze.
However, it is difficult for me to imagine how to implement this system in relation to convicts, because on average such a survey takes a month.
The doctor, despite the fact that in general the idea of creating separate blocks for transsexuals supported, also doubts that in the current economic conditions it will be advisable to allocate funds for the construction of new premises, medical examinations, - there are only a few transgender people in Russia.
It is difficult to calculate, there are no official statistics, but if we take into account that homosexuals in Russia are about 5%, then we can say that there are even fewer transgender people, and those who have such a deviation and also commit crimes are not at all a small number," Lordkipanidze said.
Now, at the request of the administration of the colony, homosexuals, transgender people can already receive separate conditions of detention.
