This year, the study of the Association of Russian Managers "Top-1000 Russian Managers" is published for the 16th time.
Being a tool for assessing the professional reputation of Russian managers of the highest echelon, the study sums up the results of the work of Russian managers for the year, identifying leaders in industries and functional areas.
The initial pool of candidates consists of the winners of the rating of the previous year.
Last year's winners are invited to confirm their participation as a candidate for the current year's rating and nominate members of their management team.
In addition, each of the candidates included in the initial list is invited to nominate up to ten new managers from other companies, whom it would be advisable to add to the general pool of candidates.
It is possible to nominate the following managers of the functional areas of the company: financial director, commercial director, marketing director, HR director, CIO, director of public and corporate relations, director of relations with authorities, director of corporate governance.
Each manager proposed by experts is sent an invitation to participate in the rating and is given the opportunity to nominate his management team and up to ten new managers from other companies.
Nomination of candidates on the sectoral principle is carried out on the basis of the industry classifier of the Association of Managers: information technology, commercial banks, forestry and timber processing industry, mechanical engineering, media business, metallurgy, diversified holdings, professional services, communications and telecommunications, service and production of consumer goods, insurance, construction, trade, transport, financial sector, pharmaceuticals, chemical industry, energy and fuel complex.
Each participant is provided with a login and password to enter the site www.top1000.amr.ru, where they see information about other participants and can put their scores on the criteria proposed for each functional area.
The methodology for building the rating is based on the principle of "The best choose the best": top managers evaluate top managers, functional managers evaluate functional managers.
Such a principle allows you to get the most authentic assessment of the professional reputation of colleagues.
The final results of the rating are approved at meetings of expert commissions.
All interested candidates of the rating of the current year and multiple candidates of the rating of previous years are invited to face-to-face meetings of expert commissions.
Commissions are organized on a functional basis: a commission for approving the list of top managers and eight commissions for approving heads of functional areas.
At the meetings of the expert commissions, it is proposed to approve the submitted lists in alphabetical order (the places are retained strictly according to the Internet assessment and are classified information until the publication of the rating) or to make updating adjustments to them in accordance with the attached list of reserve candidates.
The names of the companies are given in accordance with the rules of the Russian language and the norms of "Kommersant".
At the time of publication of the rating, changes in the status of managers and companies are possible.
A comfortable rate for investment credit is 10-13%.
According to experts, the lending market for small and medium-sized businesses in January-April of this year sank by 40%.
What, in your opinion, is the situation today?
After the panic sentiments of late 2014 - early 2015, the volume of lending to SMEs decreased significantly.
The reason is clear: a sharp increase in interest rates.
Lending at 25-30% per annum was not beneficial to anyone.
If earlier the bank could put in the increased rate all its possible problems in the future, from delays to non-returns, now it is impossible to do this: the rates are already sky-high.
For business, the current level of interest rates on SME loans is uncomfortable.
For a significant part of investment projects, the current level is unacceptable from the point of view of their payback.
The level of rates of 10-13% would allow businesses to invest in a wide range of projects and form attractive profitability on them.
To what extent, according to your estimates, is the demand of entrepreneurs for loans satisfied?
After the central bank lowered the interest rate, the situation improved slightly.
Credit resources have become more accessible.
However, according to our observations, customers began to apply for loans much less often.
First of all, the business does not understand the prospects for its development and future revenues.
Today, business has one way out: it is necessary to learn how to work, focusing on the current economic situation in the country and the region.
It is necessary to monitor the current results more closely, to control the movement of funds.
At the same time, if financial resources are available, it is worth using new technologies that allow you to modernize equipment, reduce production costs and energy supply.
All this, ultimately, allows the company to make products more competitive and keep the business even in an unstable economic situation.
What are the main trends in the SME lending market that will strengthen and influence its development by the end of 2015?
Will the interest rate change?
The forecast for lowering the average rate will largely depend on the policy of the Central Bank, and now the regulator demonstrates consistency in the issue of lowering the key rate.
However, a radical drop in the price of loans for SMEs should not be expected.
In the current situation, the problem, first of all, is inflation, which makes it necessary to increase the interest rate to obtain real income.
In addition, the cost of money in Russia will remain high even with a reduction in the rates of the Central Bank.
If we talk about the level of delinquency, then traditionally small and medium-sized businesses, limited both in the possibilities of replenishing funds and in the options for correcting economic behavior, will certainly pose a greater risk to creditors.
I would not expect a significant reduction in the share of bad loans.
The main reason is international sanctions and their negative impact on the country's economy.
