The formulas by which the cost will be calculated will be promulgated next year.
This is done in order to prevent prices from soaring by 200-300%, as it happens, for example, during the St. Petersburg Economic Forum.
You need to have a conscience and prevent a two- or three-fold increase, but hotels also need to be allowed to earn.
"I think the growth will be up to 50%," explained Gennady Lamshin, president of the Russian Hotel Association.
In turn, Vadim Vladimirov is not sure that price fixation corresponds to the understanding of a market economy.
