Thanks to the issuance of new shares at a discounted price, Glencore's share price on the London Stock Exchange soared in early morning trading on Wednesday.
The stock jumped 2.77 percent to 131.60 pence on the FTSE 100 index, which traded 0.69 percent higher at the open.
Glencore last week began selling $2.5 billion worth of shares as part of extensive plans to cut its $30 billion debt by about a third.
The company sold new shares at 125 cents apiece, a 2.4 percent discount to tuesday's close.
It placed 1.3 billion new shares, which is 9.99 percent of the company's share capital.
