Organizations whose specialists are engaged in collecting complaints from users of the social network about offensive posts should also contribute to the prompt blocking of illegal content.
The management of Facebook intends to provide them with the necessary financial support.
The decision to delete posts containing negative statements about migrants and refugees, the leadership of the social network and the Ministry of Justice of Germany was made after xenophobic sentiments sharply increased in the German segment of Facebook.
One of the most obvious reasons for them was the unprecedented migration crisis that swept the EU countries some time ago.
So, in Germany, all the points intended for the accommodation of refugees are already overcrowded.
On the eve of the country's authorities decided to temporarily settle migrants on the territory of the former Buchenwald concentration camp.
Internally displaced persons from the Middle East and Africa are housed in barracks where prisoners and prisoners of war were held under the Nazi regime.
In Moscow cemeteries there will be areas for relaxation.
In the near future, several metropolitan cemeteries will be equipped with specialized areas for relaxation and psychological rest.
Among the first will be Butovskoye, Domodedovskoye, and Shcherbinskoye cemetery.
The first zone for psychological recreation has already appeared at the Troyekurovskoye cemetery in Moscow.
In the future, similar sites will appear in other areas of the city.
This was told to the portal m24.ru Artem Ekimov, who holds the post of head of the State Budgetary Institution "Ritual".
Relaxation areas will be small green areas resembling parks.
According to experts, in such "corners" visitors to cemeteries will be able to relax, be alone with themselves and restore psychological strength.
In the near future, relaxation zones will be built in the Domodedovo, Butovsky and Shcherbinsk cemeteries, and then in other districts of the capital.
According to the head of the State Budgetary Institution "Ritual", if there is a need to expand the area of the cemetery, the builders will try to preserve the existing forest areas as much as possible.
Green spaces will serve as a living fence that will separate recreation areas and areas reserved directly for burial places.
Experts of the State Budgetary Institution "Ritual" also announced their intention to make a proposal to abandon the hedges in the graves.
New cemeteries can indeed become barrier-free.
In addition, the GBU "Ritual" told about the readiness to install electronic terminals, with the help of which visitors to cemeteries will be able to find out GPS-coordinates and license plates of burials.
In June of this year, the State Budgetary Institution "Ritual" also proposed to adjust the cost of burial services depending on the time of year.
So, digging a grave in the summer will cost a thousand rubles cheaper, weeks in winter, when the ground is frozen.
It should be noted that over the past year, prices for all types of funeral services have risen in price by an average of 10 percent.
