He has traveled a great distance at his age.
Miraculously, he survived.
The mushroom picker was taken to the Yelny Central District Hospital unconscious, in extremely serious condition.
Doctors diagnosed him with pneumonia, as well as severe dehydration and hypothermia of the body.
How an elderly man was able to stay alive after five days spent in the forest, doctors have absolutely no idea.
Valentina Nepsha, head of the therapeutic department of the Yelny CRH: "An examination of the patient, treatment is prescribed."
Infusion therapy, antibacterial.
Considering all his chronic diseases.
