The Russian-Belarusian exercises "Union Shield-2015" have ended.
In the west of the country, the joint Russian-Belarusian exercises "Shield of the Union-2015" have ended, "Russia 24" reports.
The maneuvers took place at training grounds in the Leningrad, Pskov and Kaliningrad regions, as well as in the Baltic Sea.
More than eight thousand servicemen and about four hundred units of equipment participated.
On the last day of the exercises, the ships of the Baltic Fleet practiced an artillery strike on sea and coastal targets, as well as repelling an air attack by a conditional enemy.
Where can I leave feedback about the work of a bailiff in Murmansk?
The Office of the Federal Bailiff Service for the Murmansk Region reported that in order to improve the work on protecting the rights and legitimate interests of citizens and organizations, the department has a book of reviews and suggestions.
In it, citizens can leave a record of the quality of the work of bailiffs-executors and other officials of the department, information about shortcomings in the work, as well as express their suggestions and wishes.
In management, a copy of the book of reviews and suggestions is located in the central hall, in a special pocket in a visible and accessible place at the checkpoint to the building.
In the structural units of the management, the book is located in the office.
Taking into account the nature of the withdrawal or proposal, a written response shall be sent to the initiator, as appropriate.
Xi Jinping calls for making the economy more open to the world
The economy must become more open to the world to spur growth, President Xi Jinping said on Tuesday in an address to the group tasked with leading reforms.
"China should focus on attracting foreign investors and experts and develop an opening-up policy," he said, addressing participants in the 16th meeting of the Central Leading Group Committee on Deepening Reforms Comprehensively.
According to him, the expansion of openness and deepening of reforms will give the economy a new impetus and vitality and provide a new space for economic development.
The lead group adopted a number of directives, including the introduction of regulation of investor access to the market, the amendment of border control rules, the promotion of state-owned enterprises (SOEs) attracting private capital and the revision of the resident registration system.
According to the statement, a list of sectors of the economy and production that are not available for investment will be compiled.
The system will be gradually debugged through trial programs.
This is an important step as it will give the market a more significant role in allocating resources, ensuring the rule of law in the business sphere and increasing openness, the statement said.
The government will also loosen control over the powers given to them to companies, thereby ensuring that companies conduct their own business.
The statement also said that China will allow border regions to explore new models of cross-border economic cooperation and new mechanisms to strengthen local growth.
Even more areas will be available to private investors in order to increase the openness of state-controlled sectors of the economy.
"The government will not change its policy towards foreign investors and will protect the legitimate interests of companies with foreign financing, as well as provide them with better conditions," the statement said.
In addition, the procedure for applying for a permanent residence permit for foreigners, or "green card", will be facilitated by optimizing the requirements and simplifying the filing process itself.
The meeting also discussed ensuring the rights of lawyers and training professional judges and prosecutors.
According to an official report released after the meeting, it was also attended by Premier Li Keqiang and ministers Liu Yunshan and Zhang Gaoli.
